@NODE "Short" "Short Description"
This prog convert Ms-Dos Karaoke MidiFiles to Amiga
Very usefull for midiplay, and especially Foreign langages
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Exemple" "Exemple French Kar File"
You know "C'est deja ca" ? mmh, yes It's a french song not very well...
For a long time I couldn't use it as a Karaoke file in midiplay...Try it!
See how it's bugging Midiplay???

If you next run KaraoFR on it, it will play perfectly (yes).
Why? What did KaraoFR? It just entered into the lyrics of the KAR and
changed all special foreign Characters to convert from MS-DOS to AMIGA ASCII
YES Midiplay don't handle this!! And most of the karaoke maker I
saw on PC, work on MS-DOS, and not WINDOWS that is using the same ASCII !!!!
That's why a lot of foreign songs don't play correctly...Some plays because 
they got a WINDOWS ASCII, or because they cutted the accents on letters :)
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "How to install it?"
Are you just stupid?
There are 2 files! the executable, and the exemple Kar file!
Put them where you want! let's go!
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Use" "How to use it?"
This is just an amigados command!
so give it a file name to check....
Ex: KaraoFR dh0:kars/DejaCa.Kar
or ask him to scan a whole directory...
Ex: KaraoFR dh0:kars/
ATTENTION! don't forget the final / or : otherwise it will try to scan a file

Don't hesitate to scan any directories...KaraoFR is looking inside the files
before doing something... he knows recognize a Kar file and midifiles-only...
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Who" "Who shall use it?"
I think this prob will only hit ppl that use alphabet with special chars
inside...Like me! I am FRENCH so I maked this ESSENTIAL prog for french
karaoke users (french KAR packs on ftp.midifarm.com are ALL MS-DOS!).
That's why this prog is called FR, it's why it handles all french special
chars:
            ç ŕ â ä é č ę ë î ď ô ö ů ű ü

But perhaps another language need this? e-mail me...i can add some chars ?

NEW IN VERSION 1.1 !!!! USEFULL FOR EVERY KARAOKE USERS!!!!!
In the 1.1 version I implemented a new cool function..
I noticed YET a boring thing with some KARs... There is some without any
paragraph...grrr... and then, with midiplay, you don't see the lyrics
before they come! Mmmh the only solution is to edit them....BUT!
I noticed some Kar files had some 'special paragraph' yep the paragraph
are just delimited by a 'Space' char at the start of one sentence!
So now KaraoFr is checking for them, and add the paragraph char (in fact
just \ instead of /)
I added too a translation for the char ' that is sometimes differents on PC
@ENDNODE

